## Root Cause of 6/7 Bug

The previous logic used different formulas for column width calculation:
- When `columnCount > visibleColumns`: Used `visibleColumns` in formula
- When `columnCount <= visibleColumns`: Used `columnCount` in formula (THIS WAS THE BUG)

**Example:**
If you have 5 columns and select visibleColumns = 7, the condition `5 > 7` is false, so it used `columnCount` (5) in the formula instead of `visibleColumns` (7). This made the columns stay at "5 column width" instead of "7 column width" (narrower).

**Fix:** Always use `visibleColumns` in the width calculation formula, regardless of how many columns exist.

