## Key Decisions

### 1. Always Use visibleColumns in Width Calculation
**Reasoning:**
- User expects selecting "7" to make columns narrower than "5"
- Previous logic only worked when scrolling was needed
- New logic: `visibleColumns` always determines column width, even if fewer columns exist

### 2. Horizontal Number Buttons Instead of Dropdown
**Reasoning:**
- More visual and immediate feedback
- Easier to click (no need to open dropdown)
- Shows all options at once
- Common pattern in design tools (Figma, Sketch)

### 3. Used Widget headerAccessory Prop
**Reasoning:**
- Clean API provided by Widget component
- Positions buttons perfectly in header
- Avoids DOM restructuring
- Consistent with other widget accessories

### 4. Set draggable={false} to Hide Controls
**Reasoning:**
- User explicitly requested removing rearrange/resize/delete icons
- Widget component already has this prop built-in
- Clean solution without custom CSS

